==Proof==

'''Given''': A conjugate-join-closed subnormal subgroup <math>H</math> of a group <math>G</math>, a subnormal subgroup <math>K</math> of <math>G</math>.

'''To prove''': <math>\langle H, K \rangle</math> is subnormal.

'''Proof''':

# ('''Given data used''': <math>H</math> is conjugate-join-closed subnormal in <math>G</math>): Since <math>H</math> is conjugate-join-closed subnormal in <math>G</math>, <math>H^K</math> is subnormal in <math>G</math>.
# ('''Given data used''': <math>H, K</math> are subnormal in <math>G</math>; '''Fact used''': fact (1)): By fact (1), we get that <math>\langle H, K \rangle</math> is subnormal in <math>G</math>.
